<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Archlinux Installation on ArchLinux Personal Config &amp; Documentation</title><link>http://localhost:1313/installation/</link><description>Recent content in Archlinux Installation on ArchLinux Personal Config &amp; Documentation</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-GB</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 20 Feb 2025 00:20:28 +0100</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://localhost:1313/installation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Roadmap</title><link>http://localhost:1313/installation/roadmap/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/installation/roadmap/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="installation-roadmap">Installation Roadmap &lt;a href="#installation-roadmap" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;div class="alert alert-danger d-flex" role="alert">
 &lt;div class="flex-shrink-1 alert-icon">
 &lt;span class="material-icons size-20 me-2">
 report
 &lt;/span>&lt;/div>
 &lt;div class="w-100">
&lt;p>Always consult the &lt;a href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Installation_guide" rel="external" target="_blank">Arch Wiki Installation Guide&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> for the most current procedures and troubleshooting tips as the installation process may evolve over time.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Pre-Installation</title><link>http://localhost:1313/installation/pre-installation/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/installation/pre-installation/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="pre-installation">Pre-Installation &lt;a href="#pre-installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;h4 id="preparation--research">Preparation &amp;amp; Research &lt;a href="#preparation--research" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Review the &lt;a href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Installation_guide" rel="external" target="_blank">Arch Linux Installation Guide&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> for a detailed walkthrough.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Backup any important data (recommended if working on a non empty storage).&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Download the latest Arch Linux ISO from the official &lt;a href="https://archlinux.org/download/#download-mirrors" rel="external" target="_blank">Arch Linux website&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h4 id="create-bootable-media">Create Bootable Media &lt;a href="#create-bootable-media" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;p>Use tools such as &lt;a href="https://etcher.balena.io/" rel="external" target="_blank">Balena Etcher&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://www.ventoy.net/en/index.html" rel="external" target="_blank">Ventoy&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>, or, if you prefer the command line, the &lt;code>dd&lt;/code> utility to write the ISO to a USB drive.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Installation</title><link>http://localhost:1313/installation/installation/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/installation/installation/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="installation">Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;h4 id="boot-into-the-arch-linux-live-environment">Boot into the Arch Linux Live Environment &lt;a href="#boot-into-the-arch-linux-live-environment" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;p>Boot from the USB drive and confirm you are in UEFI mode by checking for the presence of &lt;code>/sys/firmware/efi&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h4 id="set-up-the-keyboard-layout-if-needed">Set Up the Keyboard Layout (if needed) &lt;a href="#set-up-the-keyboard-layout-if-needed" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;p>You can list all available keymaps using:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="7df5172" class="language- ">
 &lt;code>localectl list-keymaps&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;p>Then set your preferred keymap:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="4e79821" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>loadkeys us&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;p>&lt;em>(replace &lt;code>us&lt;/code> with your chosen layout)&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Additionally, you can change the console font with:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>System Configuration</title><link>http://localhost:1313/installation/system-configuration/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/installation/system-configuration/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="system-configuration">System Configuration &lt;a href="#system-configuration" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;h4 id="generate-the-filesystem-table-fstab">Generate the Filesystem Table (fstab) &lt;a href="#generate-the-filesystem-table-fstab" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;p>After installing the base system, generate the filesystem table by running:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="e932261" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>genfstab -U /mnt &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /mnt/etc/fstab&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s important to review the generated &lt;code>/mnt/etc/fstab&lt;/code> file to ensure that all partitions are correctly listed and configured.&lt;/p>
&lt;h4 id="chroot-into-the-new-system">Chroot into the New System &lt;a href="#chroot-into-the-new-system" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;p>Finally, change root into your new system environment to continue with further configuration:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="de0c732" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>arch-chroot /mnt&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h4 id="time-zone-and-localization">Time Zone and Localization &lt;a href="#time-zone-and-localization" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>&lt;p>If you need to &lt;strong>set your timezone manually&lt;/strong> you can do so by creating a symlink:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Post-Installation</title><link>http://localhost:1313/installation/post-installation/</link><pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/installation/post-installation/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="reboot-and-post-installation">Reboot and Post Installation &lt;a href="#reboot-and-post-installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;h4 id="exit-chroot-and-unmount-filesystems">Exit Chroot and Unmount Filesystems &lt;a href="#exit-chroot-and-unmount-filesystems" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h4>


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="4cf65e3" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>exit # exits chroot
umount -R /mnt # not mandatory but &lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h5 id="reboot-the-system">Reboot the System &lt;a href="#reboot-the-system" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h5>&lt;p>Run: &lt;code>reboot&lt;/code> and remove the installation media when prompted.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Then, Log in as your regular user.&lt;/p>
&lt;h5 id="post-installation-tasks">Post Installation Tasks &lt;a href="#post-installation-tasks" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h5>&lt;p>After rebooting and logging in, it&amp;rsquo;s time to fine-tune your system configurations by enabling and starting essential services.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>First, ensure that the network connection remains stable by enabling the network management tool you configured earlier.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>